Lac du unclear
Jan. 11th 99
Dr. Montezuma;
Dear Friend;
I received your kind letter while at home. I thank you so much for getting me this place for I know of no one that would do me such a kindness. I cam here the 1st of Jan. I have the dearest little hospital I have six patients  but none very sick. The Doctor comes out from town two or three times a week. I like him for he is so kind, in fact all the teachers ar nice Melinda Thomas is also here as a dining room matron, she use to be a Carlisle student My, but it cold here, the snow is quite deep. The school is almost surrounded by lakes, and there's lovely skating. The say its very beautiful here ion the summer. I borrowed money from my brother to come here, its the first time I have ever asked him for
